<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="675" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d675">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2412a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Secretary of Commerce</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RWC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Redfield</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-13">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: As you are aware, this Department,
                                since February 19, 1915, in compliance with the request of the
                                German Government, has been transmitting to that Government, through
                                the American Embassy at Berlin, information concerning the sailings
                                and arrivals of American vessels, giving as complete details as
                                possible.</p>
                            <p>I now have the honor to advise you, for the information of the Bureau
                                of Navigation, that, although the Department will continue to
                                transmit such information regarding American passenger vessels, it
                                is considered inadvisable at this time to send to the German
                                Government any information concerning the departure and arrival of
                                ships carrying freight only, other than to neutral ports.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>